Kangaroo Point Bridge will be lit Purple to celebrate 120 Years of NCWQ&nbsp;
The National Council of Women of Queensland (NCWQ) is an umbrella organisation for thirty women&rsquo;s organisations. We seek to raise awareness of the rights and responsibilities of members as citizens and encourages their participation in all aspects of community life. The 120th Anniversary celebration is to acknowledge significant difference NCWQ has made with a theme of Celebrating Queensland Women&rsquo;s Voices; the legacy, leadership and change. NCWQ was started on 15th June 1905.
This Light Up is organised by: The National Council of Women of QLD (NCWQ)

